## What this is

A REST service that logs compliance events for one or more workflows (RA 12010
or similar). Persists to SQL Server via stored procedures, writes audit trail
entries, runs scheduled retry + report jobs, and integrates with an upstream
EAPI over HTTP with Resilience4j retry / circuit-breaker / timeout.

## Quick start (local)

```bash
# 1. Start SQL Server in Docker
docker run -d --name <%= projectName %>-sql \
  -e "ACCEPT_EULA=Y" -e "MSSQL_SA_PASSWORD=YourStrongPassword!" \
  -e "MSSQL_PID=Developer" -p 1433:1433 \
  mcr.microsoft.com/mssql/server:2022-latest

# 2. Create the database (default name from your CLI prompt was used here)
docker exec <%= projectName %>-sql /opt/mssql-tools18/bin/sqlcmd \
  -S localhost -U sa -P "YourStrongPassword!" -C \
  -Q "CREATE DATABASE <%= projectName.toUpperCase() %>;"

# 3. Run the application — local profile bypasses OAuth2
./mvnw spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=local
```

Flyway applies all migrations (V1, V2, R__procedures, R__triggers) on first startup.

App lives at:
- HTTP: `http://localhost:8181`
- OpenAPI UI: `http://localhost:8181/swagger-ui.html`
- Health: `http://localhost:8181/health`
- Metrics: `http://localhost:8181/prometheus`

## Run the tests

