## Conventions baked in

- **OAuth2 Resource Server** — production endpoints require `Bearer <jwt>` with
  the appropriate `scope` claim. Disabled under `local` and `test` profiles.
- **API versioning** at `/api/v1/...` via `WebConfig.addPathPrefix`.
- **Actuator at root**: `/health`, `/health/liveness`, `/health/readiness`,
  `/info`, `/metrics`, `/prometheus` (no `/actuator/` prefix).
- **Structured JSON logs** via logback pattern + `CorrelationIdFilter`.
- **PII redaction** in logs (masks anything that looks like an account number
  or customer id) as a safety net.
- **Resilience4j** wired for outbound EAPI calls (retry + circuit breaker +
  time limiter, configured in `application.yml`).
- **ShedLock** prevents duplicate `@Scheduled` execution across pods.

## Profiles

| Profile | When | Behaviour |
|---|---|---|
| `local` | Developer laptop | `LocalSecurityConfig` permits all, scheduled jobs gated off, verbose logs |
| `test` | CI / IT runs | `TestSecurityConfig` permits all, scheduled jobs gated off |
| `dev` / `staging` / `prod` | AKS clusters | OAuth2 enforced, scheduled jobs active, structured JSON logs |

